      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-grade example of the pinnacle of Japanese engineering. Power is delivered by a flawless 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting perfect compression and seamless boost transition across the secondary turbocharger engagement. The chassis maintains its original 50:50 weight distribution, complemented by a factory-spec four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for surgical cornering precision. The five-speed manual transmission features crisp gates and robust synchros, while the cooling system has been meticulously preserved to prevent any heat-soak issues common to the platform. With zero vacuum leaks and an uncompromised undercarriage, this FD is a turn-key collector\u2019s piece for the discerning enthusiast.",
